{
  "texts": [
    "These approaches aid in balancing the distribution of the classes, enhancing model accuracy, and lowering the danger of bias toward the majority class.",
    "Beluga whale optimization, or shortly BWO, is a recent swarm-based metaheuristic algorithm that takes its cues from the collective intelligence of beluga whales.",
    "Pair swimming, hunting, and calving are all metaphors for the three phases of discovery, exploitation, and extinction that occur when a whale population collapses.",
    "The self-adaptive balance factor and the probability of a whale falling regulate the rate of discovery and extraction in BWO (Zhong et al. 2022).",
    "The beluga whale, or Delphinapterus leucas, is a whale shark."
  ]
}